So the only question is

236
00:15:04,171 --> 00:15:06,765
whether you wanna lose
with 24% of the vote

237
00:15:06,807 --> 00:15:08,707
or 28%.

238
00:15:08,742 --> 00:15:10,642
You bring the numbers up,

239
00:15:10,677 --> 00:15:12,838
you look good
for the legislature--

240
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:16,077
maybe a congressional run.

241
00:15:16,116 --> 00:15:17,811
- Albert Stokes.
- Here.

242
00:15:17,851 --> 00:15:21,446
Mr. P., can I go? My moms told me to go
straight home after school.

243
00:15:21,488 --> 00:15:23,547
Mine too.

244
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:26,115
You should have thought of that
before you smeared ink

245
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:27,787
all over my desk.

246
00:15:27,828 --> 00:15:29,352
Weren't my fault.
My pen exploded.

247
00:15:31,165 --> 00:15:32,928
Michael.

248
00:15:32,966 --> 00:15:34,661
Michael Lee?

249
00:15:34,701 --> 00:15:36,931
Mr. P., please,
can I go?

250
00:15:36,970 --> 00:15:39,962
I ain't eat no lunch, and my stomach
making all these noises.

251
00:15:40,007 --> 00:15:44,501
Look, I won't ever disrespect
your pencil again, I promise.

252
00:15:44,545 --> 00:15:46,513
Zenobia, it wasn't
about the pencil.

253
00:15:46,547 --> 00:15:49,539
Please, Mr. P.

254
00:15:58,892 --> 00:16:02,760
- Okay okay, all right.
- All right.

255
00:16:02,796 --> 00:16:04,991
Just this one time,
I'll make an exception.

256
00:16:07,334 --> 00:16:10,167
But next time, expect
to stay the full hour.

257
00:16:23,083 --> 00:16:25,415
- Why are you here?
- Came to say sorry.

258
00:16:25,452 --> 00:16:28,046
I didn't mean to get
all up in your face like that.

259
00:16:29,389 --> 00:16:31,016
I appreciate that, Namond.

260
00:16:31,058 --> 00:16:33,652
It takes courage
to admit when you're wrong.

261
00:16:33,694 --> 00:16:36,857
What I can't understand-- I've seen you
in Ms. Sampson's class doing your work.

262
00:16:36,897 --> 00:16:40,060
- Why can't you do the same in here?
- I mean to, I do.

263
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:43,627
It's just the evil get in me and before
I know it, I go off.

264
00:16:45,572 --> 00:16:47,597
Well...

265
00:16:47,641 --> 00:16:49,575
tomorrow we'll see
if we can do better.

266
00:16:49,610 --> 00:16:52,272
Can't tomorrow.
Mrs. D. put me out.

267
00:16:52,312 --> 00:16:55,645
I gotta bump.
Later, Mr. P.

268
00:16:58,652 --> 00:17:01,086
If you can wait
outside...

269
00:17:01,121 --> 00:17:03,112
It's okay.
He can stay.

270
00:17:07,127 --> 00:17:08,116
Thank you.

271
00:17:09,596 --> 00:17:13,123
Mr. P., you know
Michael can't make it to detention.

272
00:17:13,166 --> 00:17:15,191
I know he didn't.
Now it's doubled.

273
00:17:15,235 --> 00:17:18,068
- He's got two days to serve.
- Nah, I mean, he can't.

274
00:17:18,105 --> 00:17:20,437
He got to go pick up
his little brother from school.

275
00:17:20,474 --> 00:17:22,669
Well, he'll just have to
find somebody else to do that.

276
00:17:24,044 --> 00:17:26,706
It-- it ain't like that.

277
00:17:26,747 --> 00:17:28,374
I mean, Michael would come
if he could,

278
00:17:28,415 --> 00:17:31,350
but wouldn't have nobody else
to pick up his little brother Bug.

279
00:17:31,385 --> 00:17:33,615
You know, his mother,
she on that stuff.

280
00:17:40,327 --> 00:17:42,261
We walking home.
You coming?

281
00:17:42,296 --> 00:17:45,857
Oh, no, I'm waiting on Alpo.
Ms. Sampson got him doing detention.

282
00:17:45,899 --> 00:17:48,197
- You gonna be here till, like, 5:00.
- Yeah, she a hard lady.

283
00:17:48,235 --> 00:17:50,100
She don't ever give
a brother no play.

284
00:17:50,137 --> 00:17:54,005
- All right. I'll holla at you later.
- All right, yo.

285
00:17:56,109 --> 00:17:58,737
So you're not gonna be
in the NBA?

286
00:17:58,779 --> 00:18:01,680
Then it must be the NFL?

287
00:18:01,715 --> 00:18:04,343
I thought all the boys in class
were gonna join the pros.

288
00:18:04,384 --> 00:18:05,942
Nah, that's just
something we say.

289
00:18:06,954 --> 00:18:09,218
So what about you?

290
00:18:09,256 --> 00:18:11,486
What do you wanna be
when you grow up?

291
00:18:11,525 --> 00:18:13,925
I'm gonna own
my own store.

292
00:18:13,961 --> 00:18:17,055
That's smart. You're gonna need
to know a lot of math.

293
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:22,999
You left them in there.

294
00:18:24,371 --> 00:18:26,635
- Oh-hh.
- Hey, don't worry, Mr. P.

295
00:18:26,673 --> 00:18:29,665
We got you.
Hey, Donut!

296
00:18:29,710 --> 00:18:32,338
- Yo, yeah.
- Donut's crazy with cars.

297
00:18:32,379 --> 00:18:33,846
He can open anything.

298
00:18:33,880 --> 00:18:35,211
- Hey. What up, man?
- Hey.

299
00:18:35,248 --> 00:18:38,376
Yo, he locked
his keys in there.

300
00:18:42,089 --> 00:18:44,353
It's okay,
I can call AAA.

301
00:18:44,391 --> 00:18:46,018
Oh, no problem, chief.

302
00:19:27,834 --> 00:19:30,166
Feel the need
to work them corners, huh?

303
00:19:32,239 --> 00:19:34,969
I'm just asking 'cause you don't need
to be doing what you're doing.

304
00:19:35,008 --> 00:19:36,942
I need to learn some shit
on my own.

305
00:19:36,977 --> 00:19:39,810
I'm trying
to help you, Sherrod,

306
00:19:39,846 --> 00:19:41,939
but you making it
so I can't.

307
00:19:41,982 --> 00:19:43,916
I didn't even know
the man who beat on you, Bubs.

308
00:19:43,950 --> 00:19:45,577
He was short money
on the corner.

309
00:19:45,619 --> 00:19:47,553
I swear he wasn't
nothing to me.

310
00:19:47,587 --> 00:19:50,818
Yeah, but when the shit start,
there's nothing to be done, right?

311
00:19:50,857 --> 00:19:53,792
What would I have done
if he started whaling on you?

312
00:19:53,827 --> 00:19:57,820
Same kind of nothing, see?
That's how the corners be.

313
00:19:59,299 --> 00:20:01,597
They going to use you up,
Sherrod.

314
00:20:06,840 --> 00:20:11,072
You welcome to stay tonight, but you
ain't in school tomorrow morning,

315
00:20:11,111 --> 00:20:13,170
this partnership need
to be done.

316
00:20:42,209 --> 00:20:44,769
These two precincts
are the bellwether for the Fifth.

317
00:20:44,811 --> 00:20:48,247
If you can take even 18%
out of Carcetti in these,

318
00:20:48,281 --> 00:20:50,749
it's a good guess he won't
have the numbers citywide.

319
00:20:50,784 --> 00:20:52,877
And who are we ticketed
with over here?

320
00:20:52,919 --> 00:20:55,979
The N.D.O.,
I hope, because...

321
00:20:57,724 --> 00:21:01,216
...this amid allegations that
high-ranking police officials intervened

322
00:21:01,261 --> 00:21:05,254
to have a veteran police detective
removed from the controversial case.

323
00:21:05,298 --> 00:21:08,529
The Braddock murder became
a focal point in the mayoral campaign

324
00:21:08,568 --> 00:21:10,900
when Councilman
Thomas Carcetti alleged

325
00:21:10,937 --> 00:21:12,928
the West Baltimore man
was killed

326
00:21:12,973 --> 00:21:15,203
because he was
a witness in the case.

327
00:21:15,242 --> 00:21:17,142
...Because they were afraid
the police would prove

328
00:21:17,177 --> 00:21:19,270
what they most fear, that
Fredro Braddock was murdered

329
00:21:19,312 --> 00:21:22,577
because he was a witness,
and the city failed to protect him.

330
00:21:24,417 --> 00:21:26,282
It's on all three channels.

331
00:21:26,319 --> 00:21:29,015
And "The Sun" and "The Post"
are both calling for comment.

332
00:21:33,326 --> 00:21:35,954
And my sources within the department say
the rank-and-file officers

333
00:21:35,996 --> 00:21:38,396
are simply appalled by this blatant
political manipulation.

334
00:21:38,431 --> 00:21:40,058
Damn, turn it up.

335
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:42,796
Hey, Greggs, you're famous.

336
00:21:42,836 --> 00:21:45,100
...is to remove
a highly-decorated veteran

337
00:21:45,138 --> 00:21:48,198
with 15 years' experience as a murder
investigator without reason...

338
00:21:48,241 --> 00:21:50,038
- That'd be me.
- Then replaced with a rookie

339
00:21:50,076 --> 00:21:52,010
who has yet to handle a single
homicide investigation...

340
00:21:52,045 --> 00:21:54,411
- That'd be you.
-...then we need to rethink...

341
00:21:54,447 --> 00:21:55,744
- The fuck I ever do to him?

342
00:22:00,253 --> 00:22:01,845
You gonna make it
too heavy, yo.

343
00:22:01,888 --> 00:22:03,719
It might work
if we make it bigger.

344
00:22:03,757 --> 00:22:05,782
It would work if we
had balsa wood, you know?

345
00:22:05,826 --> 00:22:08,590
- It's really light and strong.
- Man, you so full of--

346
00:22:08,628 --> 00:22:11,062
oh, shit.

347
00:22:16,336 --> 00:22:17,928
Zombie Master.

348
00:22:23,944 --> 00:22:25,935
Need to take us
a little walk.

349
00:22:27,180 --> 00:22:29,114
Nah, I'm good here.

350
00:22:29,149 --> 00:22:31,743
Yo. Young'uns need
to move along.

351
00:22:33,453 --> 00:22:35,717
Sure, Chris, we'll bump.

352
00:22:41,294 --> 00:22:43,421
- Yo, Snoop, your sister in my class.
- What the fuck?

353
00:22:43,463 --> 00:22:45,055
You high
or something, nigger?

354
00:22:47,033 --> 00:22:49,467
You boys be
smoking that shit?

355
00:22:52,906 --> 00:22:55,136
Hearing good things
about you.

356
00:22:55,175 --> 00:22:57,336
Say you straight up,
take care of your people,

357
00:22:57,377 --> 00:22:59,902
not begging no handouts.

358
00:22:59,946 --> 00:23:02,210
Motherfucker, you hear the nigger
talking to you,

359
00:23:02,249 --> 00:23:05,810
giving you praises and shit. You
standing here looking fucking stupid.

360
00:23:05,852 --> 00:23:08,150
Yo, chill.

361
00:23:08,188 --> 00:23:09,917
Sometimes
she get a little hot.

362
00:23:09,956 --> 00:23:12,982
I'm just saying
the boy ain't right!

363
00:23:13,026 --> 00:23:15,961
Yo, we always in the market
for a good soldier.

364
00:23:15,996 --> 00:23:19,397
When we see one we like,
we take care of the situation--

365
00:23:19,432 --> 00:23:22,629
take him in, school him,
make him family.

366
00:23:22,669 --> 00:23:24,432
And if you're with us,
you're with us,

367
00:23:24,471 --> 00:23:27,167
just like we'd be
with you all the way.

368
00:23:27,207 --> 00:23:28,799
You have a mind,
you're in.

369
00:23:29,843 --> 00:23:32,471
Look, man.
I already got a family--

370
00:23:32,512 --> 00:23:35,140
my moms
and my little brother.

371
00:23:35,181 --> 00:23:38,082
Yeah, heard that.

372
00:23:38,118 --> 00:23:40,109
But think on it.

373
00:23:43,323 --> 00:23:45,621
We'll be around
if you need something.

374
00:23:59,739 --> 00:24:01,707
He saw me, yo. I knew it.

375
00:24:01,741 --> 00:24:03,641
I knew Chris was asking Michael
about me.

376
00:24:03,677 --> 00:24:05,304
I knew it, man.
I'm dead.

377
00:24:08,248 --> 00:24:09,681
- Yo, man, good looking out.
- Yeah.

378
00:24:09,716 --> 00:24:11,684
- I thought they was gonna--
- Yeah, I know, I know.

379
00:24:11,718 --> 00:24:14,050
What-what he ask about me?
I know he asked about me.

380
00:24:14,087 --> 00:24:15,987
- What'd you say? What'd you tell him?
- Calm down,

381
00:24:16,022 --> 00:24:17,614
- it weren't even about you.
- Yo, for real,

382
00:24:17,657 --> 00:24:20,251
you need to tell me.
What did he ask you?

383
00:24:21,661 --> 00:24:25,153
Yo, you right, man.
Chris was all up in your business.

384
00:24:25,198 --> 00:24:27,462
He down on you
for some deep shit, man.

385
00:24:27,500 --> 00:24:30,196
I don't even know what.

386
00:24:31,771 --> 00:24:33,966
Nah, I'm just fucking
with you, man.

387
00:24:34,007 --> 00:24:36,703
He didn't even
speak your name.

388
00:24:43,383 --> 00:24:45,374
Oh, man.

389
00:24:48,288 --> 00:24:52,224
So, Erv, what's next? Your officers
gonna shoot a couple of tourists?

390
00:24:52,258 --> 00:24:55,159
Maybe fly a helicopter
into Harbor Place?

391
00:24:55,195 --> 00:24:59,063
What can we expect the last week
of my re-election campaign?

392
00:24:59,099 --> 00:25:00,964
Sir, I did what you asked--
no more, no less.

393
00:25:01,001 --> 00:25:03,196
Hamsterdam--
legalized drug zone?

394
00:25:03,236 --> 00:25:04,999
Oh, he takes responsibility
for that.

395
00:25:05,038 --> 00:25:07,336
- The subpoenas all over town.
- That, too.

396
00:25:07,374 --> 00:25:10,502
Well, then the leak about the witness
murder. That was his shop too, right?

397
00:25:10,543 --> 00:25:13,068
- Hell, yeah.
- And now this last thing,

398
00:25:13,113 --> 00:25:17,880
transferring detectives off the case--
what is that? What is that?

399
00:25:17,917 --> 00:25:20,385
- Scuttling the investigation.
- Yeah, right.

400
00:25:20,420 --> 00:25:23,184
- Yeah, that's awful-- Jesus!
- Mr. Mayor, you asked me

401
00:25:23,223 --> 00:25:26,021
- to slow that investigation down.
- Mm-mmm, mm-mmm.

402
00:25:26,059 --> 00:25:28,323
Subtle, Ervin. Hmm?

403
00:25:28,361 --> 00:25:30,659
You hold a few facts
for a few weeks.

404
00:25:30,697 --> 00:25:33,666
You put a report or two
in a desk drawer.

405
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:36,032
But the transferring
of people off a case?!

406
00:25:36,069 --> 00:25:38,936
Look, you told me...

407
00:25:38,972 --> 00:25:40,803
you specifically
wanted me to not--

408
00:25:40,840 --> 00:25:42,933
Ervin, you may leave.

409
00:25:42,976 --> 00:25:47,675
- Mr. Mayor--
- That will be all, Commissioner.

410
00:25:57,824 --> 00:26:00,088
Nuh-uh.

411
00:26:00,126 --> 00:26:03,926
No, I need a word or two
with your deputy, Ervin.

412
00:26:16,276 --> 00:26:17,937
Have a seat.

413
00:26:25,718 --> 00:26:27,686
I tried to warn him.

414
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:30,188
I mean, if it leaked out of Homicide
about the dead witness,

415
00:26:30,223 --> 00:26:32,248
why wouldn't it leak that we
bumped a detective?

416
00:26:32,292 --> 00:26:33,850
Why didn't you come to us
beforehand?

417
00:26:35,628 --> 00:26:38,859
I'm a loyal subordinate,
Mr. Mayor,

418
00:26:38,898 --> 00:26:41,765
and Ervin is a good man working
under considerable pressure.

419
00:26:41,801 --> 00:26:43,200
He's a hack.

420
00:26:43,236 --> 00:26:45,670
You're not bothered
by the pressure, Deputy?

421
00:26:45,705 --> 00:26:47,696
Not in the least.

422
00:26:53,079 --> 00:26:55,377
I need you to make this
go away, Bill.

423
00:26:55,415 --> 00:26:58,179
I won't forget,
believe me.

424
00:27:09,996 --> 00:27:12,931
Another thing-- Slim Charles
got up with me.

425
00:27:12,966 --> 00:27:14,797
Said the fat man
want a sitdown.

426
00:27:14,834 --> 00:27:16,859
Nah. I did that already.

427
00:27:16,903 --> 00:27:20,771
Well, Slim say the fat man knew
the card game was gonna get took.

428
00:27:20,807 --> 00:27:23,742
He did, did he?
Set it up.

429
00:27:23,776 --> 00:27:26,267
Why you always
be back here?

430
00:27:26,312 --> 00:27:28,542
Quiet. And I can see
what comes.

431
00:27:28,581 --> 00:27:30,913
But you out in the weather
and shit.

432
00:27:30,950 --> 00:27:33,510
- I don't like to speak in no rooms.
- Yeah.

433
00:27:33,553 --> 00:27:35,453
Yo, oh-oh,
you ain't staying long.

434
00:27:38,625 --> 00:27:41,389
So you know,
I almost got that for you.

435
00:27:41,427 --> 00:27:43,019
I just need
a couple of days more.

436
00:27:43,062 --> 00:27:44,996
You can keep my money
for now.

437
00:27:45,031 --> 00:27:48,262
- I got something that needs doing.
- Anything, Marlo-- your call.

438
00:27:48,301 --> 00:27:51,998
Omar gonna come in your store,
stick it up, rob you.

439
00:27:52,038 --> 00:27:56,407
You gonna call the police,
make a report. You feel me?

440
00:27:56,442 --> 00:27:59,206
Yeah, that'll work, but, uh,
you know when he get out,

441
00:27:59,245 --> 00:28:01,679
he's coming right at me,
I ain't scared or nothing.

442
00:28:01,714 --> 00:28:03,875
- I'm just saying, you know?
- He ain't gonna get out.

443
00:28:11,791 --> 00:28:13,918
A man make bail on robbery.

444
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:16,485
Make it no bail.

445
00:28:19,499 --> 00:28:21,899
If you have a problem,

446
00:28:21,935 --> 00:28:23,835
Iike you can't make it
to detention,

447
00:28:23,870 --> 00:28:25,861
you need to tell me.

448
00:28:25,905 --> 00:28:27,532
That's your responsibility.

449
00:28:27,574 --> 00:28:30,372
People will be more than willing
to help you out,

450
00:28:30,410 --> 00:28:32,401
but it's up to you to ask.

451
00:28:33,813 --> 00:28:35,804
You can go back
to the cafeteria...

452
00:28:36,983 --> 00:28:38,644
or hang up here.

453
00:28:49,028 --> 00:28:51,997
Duquan,
could you come here?

454
00:29:03,076 --> 00:29:06,876
I thought maybe you could help me out--
I packed too much.

455
00:29:27,200 --> 00:29:28,827
Take this down
to the cafeteria

456
00:29:28,868 --> 00:29:30,927
and get yourself something to drink
from the machine.

457
00:29:30,970 --> 00:29:33,165
Thank you.

458
00:29:42,248 --> 00:29:45,217
Crystal,
you got a second?

459
00:29:46,986 --> 00:29:49,352
What's up with Duquan?

460
00:29:49,389 --> 00:29:51,823
I gave him some new clothes.
I was expecting--

461
00:29:51,858 --> 00:29:53,951
He might have lost them.

462
00:29:53,993 --> 00:29:55,984
That fast?

463
00:29:56,996 --> 00:29:58,759
It weren't that.

464
00:29:58,798 --> 00:30:01,995
His people take his clothes,
sell it on the corners.

465
00:30:02,035 --> 00:30:03,969
- You're kidding.
- No, sir.

466
00:30:04,003 --> 00:30:05,994
Everybody knows.

467
00:30:09,742 --> 00:30:11,539
Which brings me to
what we're proposing--

468
00:30:11,577 --> 00:30:13,340
different kids,
different approaches.

469
00:30:13,379 --> 00:30:15,973
You tell us who we need to touch
at North Avenue to get the go-ahead.

470
00:30:16,015 --> 00:30:17,744
The "Puzzle Palace"?

471
00:30:17,784 --> 00:30:21,413
Look, if y'all still wanna jump in
and help, I'm fine with it.

472
00:30:21,454 --> 00:30:23,479
That's about all the okay
you need in my house.

473
00:30:25,391 --> 00:30:28,792
The Stricker Street situation is
waiting in the office.

474
00:30:30,730 --> 00:30:33,893
Neighborhood squabbles,
and my babies bring it in here.

475
00:30:33,933 --> 00:30:37,528
Two fights yesterday-- all because
the mothers can't get along.

476
00:30:37,570 --> 00:30:39,333
I gotta go.

477
00:30:39,372 --> 00:30:42,034
Mrs. Donnelly will work out
the nuts and bolts.

478
00:30:43,509 --> 00:30:46,410
But just so you hear it,
thank you.

479
00:30:46,446 --> 00:30:50,109
It'll be the only time anyone
in this system will think to say it.

480
00:30:53,586 --> 00:30:55,577
He's a good man.
You need to protect him.

481
00:30:55,621 --> 00:30:57,714
- Protect him?
- Principal Withers

482
00:30:57,757 --> 00:30:59,384
just went out on a limb for you,

483
00:30:59,425 --> 00:31:02,553
and in this system they know
how to handle a chainsaw.

484
00:31:02,595 --> 00:31:04,324
Excuse me?

485
00:31:04,364 --> 00:31:06,389
Anyone has a problem
with what we're doing,

486
00:31:06,432 --> 00:31:08,400
it's on him.

487
00:31:08,434 --> 00:31:11,403
So you specified
eighth-graders?

488
00:31:11,437 --> 00:31:15,669
We have 256 on roll.

489
00:31:15,708 --> 00:31:17,903
241 attend
on a regular basis.

490
00:31:17,944 --> 00:31:21,209
Of those, 40 or so would fit your bill
of corner kids.

491
00:31:21,247 --> 00:31:23,147
40?

492
00:31:24,817 --> 00:31:26,978
Pretty workable.

493
00:31:27,019 --> 00:31:29,214
Ahem.

494
00:31:29,255 --> 00:31:31,985
- What would you suggest?
- Start with 10 or so.

495
00:31:32,024 --> 00:31:33,651
Ms. Sampson has enough
to get you going.

496
00:31:33,693 --> 00:31:36,457
- One of them named Namond Brice?
- Pick of the litter.

497
00:31:36,496 --> 00:31:38,896
But you'll have to wait.
He's on a three-day suspension.

498
00:31:38,931 --> 00:31:41,525
Tilghman Middle School.
Can I help you?

499
00:31:49,475 --> 00:31:53,070
Remember when I was a cadet,
I was up here on a cadaver search.

500
00:31:53,112 --> 00:31:54,875
Instructor gets
on the radio to say,

501
00:31:54,914 --> 00:31:57,348
"We're looking for
one body in particular.

502
00:31:57,383 --> 00:32:00,750
If you go grabbing
everyone you see,

503
00:32:00,787 --> 00:32:02,982
we'll be here all day," he says.

504
00:32:03,022 --> 00:32:05,320
Leakin Park...

505
00:32:05,358 --> 00:32:07,792
where West Baltimore
brings out its dead.

506
00:32:07,827 --> 00:32:10,625
Not anymore,
from the look of things.

507
00:32:10,663 --> 00:32:12,824
Not by the roadside,
anyway.

508
00:32:15,067 --> 00:32:16,898
If he's dumping them here,

509
00:32:16,936 --> 00:32:18,801
he's dumping them
deep in the woods.

510
00:32:21,541 --> 00:32:23,338
Come on.

511
00:32:23,376 --> 00:32:27,210
At each raid site,
we're anticipating dope

512
00:32:27,246 --> 00:32:29,544
or cash or guns.

513
00:32:29,582 --> 00:32:31,948
All warrants are
for prime locations

514
00:32:31,984 --> 00:32:34,475
Iinked to high-level
violators.

515
00:32:34,520 --> 00:32:37,546
Weeks-old addresses linked
to low-level corner boys.

516
00:32:37,590 --> 00:32:39,956
We'll also be sweeping drug corners
at these locations.

517
00:32:39,992 --> 00:32:42,688
Wagons will hold
in this location here.

518
00:32:42,728 --> 00:32:45,322
Jump-off time--
1500 hours.

519
00:32:45,364 --> 00:32:48,697
We take our position
10 minutes before the assault here.

520
00:32:48,734 --> 00:32:50,702
The go is on my say-so.

521
00:32:52,572 --> 00:32:54,631
Questions? Excellent.

522
00:32:54,674 --> 00:32:57,438
We'll hold in the rec room
till it's time to stage.

523
00:33:03,850 --> 00:33:05,681
Warrants are one thing,

524
00:33:05,718 --> 00:33:08,448
but street sweeps on Marlo Stanfield's
crews? Are you guys serious?

525
00:33:08,488 --> 00:33:10,456
Carv, you give these hoodleheads
too much credit.

526
00:33:10,490 --> 00:33:12,151
Trust me on this, Boy Wonder.

527
00:33:12,191 --> 00:33:15,354
Never mind this horseshit.

528
00:33:15,394 --> 00:33:17,328
So what've they got you
doing for your man?

529
00:33:17,363 --> 00:33:19,490
Who, the lieutenant?

530
00:33:19,532 --> 00:33:22,695
No, Royce. Herc, the mayor's
your meal ticket.

531
00:33:22,735 --> 00:33:25,329
He gets another four years,
you're liable to wear the gold braid.

532
00:33:25,371 --> 00:33:27,931
Shouldn't you be out
waving a campaign sign or some shit?

533
00:33:33,212 --> 00:33:36,773
And so ends the last crusade
of the Major Crimes Unit--

534
00:33:36,816 --> 00:33:38,750
with a whimper.

535
00:33:38,784 --> 00:33:43,221
Lester would cry to see his wiretap
cannibalized for that crap.

536
00:33:43,256 --> 00:33:46,419
Street sweeps
on Marlo Stanfield?

537
00:33:49,829 --> 00:33:52,127
- So what else you got cooking?
- Narcotics cases?

538
00:33:52,164 --> 00:33:56,362
C.I.D. has the Burman indictment
coming in. Nothing past that.

539
00:33:56,402 --> 00:33:59,963
As wars go, this drug thing
seems to rate less and less.

540
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:04,534
If Demper wins and manages
to forgive my trespasses,

541
00:34:04,577 --> 00:34:06,602
maybe I'll go in and beg
for something new.

542
00:34:06,646 --> 00:34:10,912
I don't know. Just feels like
enough's enough.

543
00:34:12,685 --> 00:34:15,153
Crutchfield, line two, lntake.

544
00:34:18,824 --> 00:34:21,725
- Sergeant, you were looking for me?
- I was, yeah.

545
00:34:21,761 --> 00:34:25,697
Curly fry?
Chicken doohickey?

546
00:34:25,731 --> 00:34:28,165
Sit down.

547
00:34:32,805 --> 00:34:35,365
Norris is back
on the Braddock case.

548
00:34:36,475 --> 00:34:38,375
It's by order
of the deputy ops.

549
00:34:38,411 --> 00:34:40,470
In fact, we're gonna go
with a story that says

550
00:34:40,513 --> 00:34:43,573
he was never off the case,
that you and he are partnered,

551
00:34:43,616 --> 00:34:46,312
a task force of two,
working it together.

552
00:34:47,720 --> 00:34:50,689
Fuck you, fat man.

553
00:34:50,723 --> 00:34:54,591
Not original, but succinct.
I like your approach.

554
00:34:54,627 --> 00:34:57,289
Y'all humiliate me once
by dropping me into this thing,

555
00:34:57,330 --> 00:35:00,390
and now you're gonna shame me again
by bringing Norris back.

556
00:35:14,981 --> 00:35:16,471
This is Homicide, Detective.

557
00:35:16,515 --> 00:35:19,313
This is not some boiler room unit
where no one pays attention

558
00:35:19,352 --> 00:35:21,343
to whatever the fuck it is
you call police work.

559
00:35:21,387 --> 00:35:24,185
The bosses?
They know our names up here.

560
00:35:24,223 --> 00:35:27,818
Now I didn't like it
when they came to me

561
00:35:27,860 --> 00:35:30,795
and told me to dump Norris,
but dump him I did.

562
00:35:30,830 --> 00:35:32,798
And it's not like I wanna
carry water for them

563
00:35:32,832 --> 00:35:35,392
now that they're pretending
they never told me to do any such thing,

564
00:35:35,434 --> 00:35:37,868
but carry the water I will.
And in the end,

565
00:35:37,903 --> 00:35:41,100
when everyone else in this unit
is buried and beshitted,

566
00:35:41,140 --> 00:35:44,632
this detective sergeant
will still be standing.

567
00:35:46,612 --> 00:35:49,638
So get the story straight:

568
00:35:49,682 --> 00:35:51,377
Norris was always
the primary,

569
00:35:51,417 --> 00:35:53,476
and you are now assisting
on an investigation

570
00:35:53,519 --> 00:35:56,317
which is progressing
even as we speak.

571
00:35:56,355 --> 00:35:58,186
Does the colonel
know about this?

572
00:35:59,992 --> 00:36:02,119
He's in the hospital--

573
00:36:02,161 --> 00:36:04,152
chemo didn't work.

574
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:10,394
Press conference is upstairs
in half an hour.

575
00:36:10,436 --> 00:36:12,563
- So don't be late.
- Press conference?

576
00:36:12,605 --> 00:36:14,766
Mm-hmm.

577
00:36:20,546 --> 00:36:23,276
I ain't mean
to laugh at you none.

578
00:36:23,315 --> 00:36:26,409
I know it sound crazy,
but I ain't joking.

579
00:36:26,452 --> 00:36:28,352
For real, Lex a zombie.

580
00:36:28,387 --> 00:36:30,287
I knew it way before
what Na' and them was saying.

581
00:36:30,322 --> 00:36:32,916
Listen,

582
00:36:32,958 --> 00:36:35,620
they had me tell Lex to go up
to the playground.

583
00:36:35,661 --> 00:36:37,561
I told him to go up there
and see some girl.

584
00:36:37,596 --> 00:36:40,759
He ain't never come
back down.

585
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:43,667
So what they gonna do to me
when they get mad at me?

586
00:36:43,703 --> 00:36:46,194
It makes sense Chris taking them
into the vacants--

587
00:36:46,238 --> 00:36:48,468
to change them.
And you know what else?

588
00:36:48,507 --> 00:36:50,134
That ain't
what he doing--

589
00:36:50,176 --> 00:36:53,236
Chris in the vacants.

590
00:36:53,279 --> 00:36:55,042
Changing them?

591
00:36:55,081 --> 00:36:56,810
He ain't changing them,
he killing them.

592
00:36:56,849 --> 00:36:59,010
That's all.
They're getting killed.

593
00:36:59,051 --> 00:37:01,042
How you know?

594
00:37:03,289 --> 00:37:05,689
Can't tell nobody.

595
00:37:07,026 --> 00:37:09,756
I seen it.

596
00:37:09,795 --> 00:37:12,355
I seen them walk
a boy up into one house

597
00:37:12,398 --> 00:37:14,025
over there on Calhoun.

598
00:37:14,066 --> 00:37:16,057
You seen that?

599
00:37:17,069 --> 00:37:19,401
Yeah.

600
00:37:19,438 --> 00:37:20,962
That's just false.

601
00:37:21,006 --> 00:37:23,167
Detective Norris has been
working in this case nonstop.

602
00:37:23,209 --> 00:37:25,336
And given her narcotics
expertise,

603
00:37:25,377 --> 00:37:27,902
Detective Greggs
was assigned to augment

604
00:37:27,947 --> 00:37:29,642
rather than to replace him.

605
00:37:29,682 --> 00:37:32,446
But for two days sources
inside the department were saying--

606
00:37:32,485 --> 00:37:35,147
I'm inside the department,
and I'm telling you that's not true.

607
00:37:35,187 --> 00:37:38,247
We do not play politics
with a criminal investigation.

608
00:37:38,290 --> 00:37:40,918
And how do you explain
Councilman Gray's allegations?

609
00:37:40,960 --> 00:37:43,656
I think you should ask
Councilman Gray that question.

610
00:37:50,136 --> 00:37:53,936
- Police! Search warrant!
- Take the back.

611
00:37:53,973 --> 00:37:56,703
- On the ground, now!
- Police! Search warrant!

612
00:37:56,742 --> 00:37:58,437
Two upstairs.

613
00:38:01,313 --> 00:38:03,042
- Don't move!
- Check that backroom.

614
00:38:03,082 --> 00:38:04,310
I said, get your ass
on the ground.

615
00:38:04,350 --> 00:38:05,374
- Get down!
- Get down!

616
00:38:15,661 --> 00:38:19,620
- This is the 1300 block, right?
- No, this is the 12.

617
00:38:19,665 --> 00:38:21,394
Are we on the right corner?

618
00:38:23,068 --> 00:38:25,400
- We had this as a stash house?
- According to the wiretap.

619
00:38:25,437 --> 00:38:27,405
How long ago?
They move them around, you know.

620
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:37,241
- Zeroes on the warrants.
- Minor arrests

621
00:38:37,283 --> 00:38:39,945
- on the designated corners, sir.
- They were tipped!

622
00:38:39,985 --> 00:38:42,010
- You think?
- For us to come up this empty

623
00:38:42,054 --> 00:38:43,544
at all these locations,
it has to be.

624
00:38:43,589 --> 00:38:45,853
This cocksucker Marlo thinks
he's smarter than us?

625
00:38:45,891 --> 00:38:48,689
He is not. Sergeant, I want
to know where he hangs.

626
00:38:48,727 --> 00:38:50,820
You mean like him personally?

627
00:38:50,863 --> 00:38:52,888
He moves around,
Lieutenant. He floats.

628
00:38:52,932 --> 00:38:55,162
But I have seen him
in the concrete park behind Fulton.

629
00:38:55,201 --> 00:38:56,862
- In a park?
- If the weather's right, he sits

630
00:38:56,902 --> 00:38:58,233
out there in some lawn chairs,
holds court.

631
00:38:58,270 --> 00:39:00,101
He's got people covering
every approach

632
00:39:00,139 --> 00:39:02,972
so there's no creeping up on him. My
guess is that he likes to talk outdoors

633
00:39:03,008 --> 00:39:04,737
so no one can drop
a microphone on him.

634
00:39:04,777 --> 00:39:08,474
Sergeant, what can
we do with that?

635
00:39:15,621 --> 00:39:18,249
I admit I've made
some mistakes,

636
00:39:18,290 --> 00:39:20,121
Burrell being
one of the biggest.

637
00:39:20,159 --> 00:39:23,219
But he's got a job
for about 10 more days.

638
00:39:23,262 --> 00:39:27,096
After the primary,
he's gone, believe me.

639
00:39:27,132 --> 00:39:30,226
And that last stunt--
pulling a detective.

640
00:39:30,269 --> 00:39:33,170
- What'd you expect?
- Not that-- huh-uh.

641
00:39:34,540 --> 00:39:38,067
Hey, I had nothing to do
with that nonsense.

642
00:39:38,110 --> 00:39:41,136
Now, that's a straight-up lie. I was
at that damn meeting when you told him,

643
00:39:41,180 --> 00:39:43,808
- "Slow the case down."
- I didn't mean--

644
00:39:43,849 --> 00:39:46,875
Who the hell knows
what you mean anymore, Clarence?

645
00:39:46,919 --> 00:39:48,910
Look at this.

646
00:39:49,955 --> 00:39:52,219
Look at it!

647
00:39:52,258 --> 00:39:55,022
You gave me
your word on this--

648
00:39:55,060 --> 00:39:57,119
your word, Clarence.

649
00:39:57,162 --> 00:40:00,427
But here you are ticketed up
with Eunetta in her best precincts

650
00:40:00,466 --> 00:40:02,934
and then ticketed up
with my girl Daniels

651
00:40:02,968 --> 00:40:04,595
where she's
running strong.

652
00:40:04,637 --> 00:40:06,901
Odell, this is the first
I've seen this.

653
00:40:06,939 --> 00:40:10,636
Come on, now! This is probably
Eunetta's people pulling this shit.

654
00:40:10,676 --> 00:40:13,076
With a "Citizens for Royce"
authority line?

655
00:40:13,112 --> 00:40:16,809
Eh, look at you, Clarence.
Just look at you.

656
00:40:16,849 --> 00:40:20,580
You've forgotten your agenda.
You've forgotten your base.

657
00:40:20,619 --> 00:40:22,587
You think a shave

658
00:40:22,621 --> 00:40:24,851
and some Marcus Garvey posters
are gonna get you over?

659
00:40:24,890 --> 00:40:26,949
Do you think that's gonna
make up for jumping in bed

660
00:40:26,992 --> 00:40:28,653
with every damn
developer?

661
00:40:28,694 --> 00:40:32,824
Shit. You're even
on Clay Davis's tit.

662
00:40:32,865 --> 00:40:35,857
Now don't you go getting
all self-righteous with me, Odell.

663
00:40:35,901 --> 00:40:38,335
Campaign runs on dollars--
you know it.

664
00:40:38,370 --> 00:40:41,635
Whose dollars?! Those sons of bitches
you got around your card table

665
00:40:41,674 --> 00:40:44,802
every month feeding your kitty?
Oh, yeah,

666
00:40:44,843 --> 00:40:48,939
I know about that too.
You-- trouble with you--

667
00:40:48,981 --> 00:40:53,475
fuck you, Clarence. I'm gonna
sit what's left of this one out.

668
00:40:53,519 --> 00:40:56,044
- I'm gonna sit it out.
- Sit it out.

669
00:40:56,088 --> 00:40:59,057
- The primary?
- Sit it out!

670
00:40:59,091 --> 00:41:01,958
Odell!
Odell!

671
00:41:01,994 --> 00:41:04,189
Who the hell do you
think you are, huh?

672
00:41:04,229 --> 00:41:06,663
Come November, I'm still gonna be
the only game in town!

673
00:41:06,699 --> 00:41:09,293
Odell, turn your back on me now,
I won't forget!

674
00:41:09,335 --> 00:41:12,498
We can't afford this.
We need his organization on Tuesday.

675
00:41:12,538 --> 00:41:14,506
- Go after him!
- Fuck that

676
00:41:14,540 --> 00:41:17,338
holier-than-thou
motherfucker!

677
00:41:18,711 --> 00:41:22,909
Delegate Watkins.
Delegate Watkins!

678
00:41:22,948 --> 00:41:24,677
Wait, sir.

679
00:41:24,717 --> 00:41:27,777
I-I'm sure we can
work this out.

680
00:41:27,820 --> 00:41:29,583
You and the mayor
can talk this through.

681
00:41:40,332 --> 00:41:42,323
Deputy Rawls, please.

682
00:41:43,402 --> 00:41:45,996
It's Lieutenant Hoskins
at the Hall.

683
00:42:07,326 --> 00:42:09,385
You're gonna use the hole
in the wall, right?

684
00:42:09,428 --> 00:42:12,295
Yeah, I'm gonna rub some dogshit
on the front of this thing.

685
00:42:12,331 --> 00:42:14,322
I don't want nobody
touching it.

686
00:42:17,336 --> 00:42:19,964
Got it?

687
00:42:27,746 --> 00:42:29,577
You need
to raise it a bit.

688
00:42:38,590 --> 00:42:40,285
Yeah, that's good.
Right there, that works.

689
00:42:45,097 --> 00:42:47,964
- Thought I heard something.
- Rats.

690
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:49,695
- How we doing?
- We need to go.

691
00:43:30,909 --> 00:43:33,469
He ain't nothing
but a skanky-ass bitch to begin with.

692
00:43:33,512 --> 00:43:35,139
And besides,
he ex-police.

693
00:43:35,180 --> 00:43:37,910
So you know what that like.

694
00:43:37,950 --> 00:43:39,815
I'm going to the ladies' room.

695
00:43:39,852 --> 00:43:42,286
Bey, you need to talk to him.

696
00:43:43,322 --> 00:43:45,950
Visiting hours
end in 30 minutes.

697
00:43:45,991 --> 00:43:48,118
- Visiting hours...
- Yo, Daddy, don't even go there,

698
00:43:48,160 --> 00:43:51,186
with you all the time telling me
how you dropped out in the sixth grade,

699
00:43:51,230 --> 00:43:53,061
went up on the corner
with Avon and Stringer,

700
00:43:53,098 --> 00:43:55,430
earned cheese for the family, saying
how it made you a man--

701
00:43:55,467 --> 00:43:57,401
All right, all right.
You right.

702
00:43:57,436 --> 00:43:59,802
Can't throw rocks.
But I'm just saying,

703
00:43:59,838 --> 00:44:02,306
you know how your mother be,
with all the fussing.

704
00:44:02,341 --> 00:44:06,243
Maybe you just need to slow it up.
You know what I'm saying?

705
00:44:06,278 --> 00:44:08,473
Yo, you heard
how Marlo punked Bodie?

706
00:44:08,514 --> 00:44:10,914
Said he either got to work for him
or give up his corner.

707
00:44:10,949 --> 00:44:13,417
Don't you know?
His sorry ass buckled.

708
00:44:13,452 --> 00:44:15,511
Oh-hh, you'd have gone
about it different?

709
00:44:15,554 --> 00:44:18,182
Yeah, I'd have
stood tall, like you.

710
00:44:18,223 --> 00:44:20,020
Got my nine--
fuck Chris and them.

711
00:44:20,058 --> 00:44:22,891
Listen to you,
all spit and fire.

712
00:44:22,928 --> 00:44:24,828
You'd have gone to the mattress
all by your lonesome

713
00:44:24,863 --> 00:44:27,388
and went up against
half of the West side.

714
00:44:27,432 --> 00:44:30,924
You got it where it counts,
and I respect that more than anything.

715
00:44:30,969 --> 00:44:34,496
But shit out there now ain't like
it was when we was coming up.

716
00:44:34,540 --> 00:44:38,101
Back in the day, a punk nigger
like Marlo steps out,

717
00:44:38,143 --> 00:44:41,510
breaking the rules and shit, he find
himself in the back of a car trunk

718
00:44:41,547 --> 00:44:43,811
on the way to Leakin Park.
No doubt.

719
00:44:43,849 --> 00:44:46,682
We did that shit right.
Word was your bond.

720
00:44:46,718 --> 00:44:49,846
Man looked out for his own,
knowing he in a family.

721
00:44:49,888 --> 00:44:51,583
Dig where
I'm coming from?

722
00:44:51,623 --> 00:44:54,786
But today
it's all fucked up.

723
00:45:11,243 --> 00:45:13,575
These steps.

724
00:45:13,612 --> 00:45:15,910
- Thank you, baby.
- You're good to go.

725
00:45:40,639 --> 00:45:43,631
Say "Omar."

726
00:45:43,675 --> 00:45:45,199
Omar.

727
00:45:57,522 --> 00:46:00,082
Nothing?

728
00:46:00,125 --> 00:46:02,093
We checked both sides
of the street

729
00:46:02,127 --> 00:46:04,186
- from here up to Monroe.
- Nothing?

730
00:46:04,229 --> 00:46:06,163
Nothing that don't
belong in no sewer.

731
00:46:06,198 --> 00:46:07,790
Thanks.

732
00:46:14,506 --> 00:46:16,599
Other ideas?

733
00:46:16,642 --> 00:46:18,303
Whoo!

734
00:46:22,014 --> 00:46:25,609
Blood, bump me off that nigger
up the "skreet."

735
00:46:25,651 --> 00:46:27,619
Motherfucker
in the "Bruick"?

736
00:46:27,653 --> 00:46:29,518
That be him.
I be saying,

737
00:46:29,554 --> 00:46:32,318
no motherfucker gonna
run off with my "hairon."

738
00:46:32,357 --> 00:46:34,222
Oh, this is
fucking great.

739
00:46:34,259 --> 00:46:37,956
Get somebody who reads lips,
this motherfucker's history.

740
00:46:37,996 --> 00:46:40,692
Is this legal-- I mean,
intercepting what they're saying?

741
00:46:40,732 --> 00:46:43,326
Don't go Freamon on me.

742
00:46:45,003 --> 00:46:47,904
Shit. I got to run.

743
00:46:47,939 --> 00:46:50,669
Hey, man, what about some
fucking relief? I been here all morning!

744
00:47:12,464 --> 00:47:16,491
You heard?
They making movies.

745
00:47:16,535 --> 00:47:19,333
Yeah. How you
wanna play it?

746
00:47:19,371 --> 00:47:22,738
I ain't sure.
Let's see the fat man.

747
00:47:24,009 --> 00:47:26,170
How'd the other thing
turn out?

748
00:47:26,211 --> 00:47:28,202
All good.

749
00:47:32,384 --> 00:47:34,352
- Yo.
- What up, boy?

750
00:47:34,386 --> 00:47:36,479
- If you want some, I got Reeses.
- Nah, man.

751
00:47:36,521 --> 00:47:39,217
You trying to make
some real cheese? $5?

752
00:47:39,257 --> 00:47:43,523
- What you need?
- Me and Paul gonna get it on with Tiff.

753
00:47:43,562 --> 00:47:45,894
Keep an eye out. I don't want Mrs. D
creeping up. Feel me?

754
00:47:45,931 --> 00:47:48,832
I feel you, but I got some sixth-graders
waiting on a special order.

755
00:47:48,867 --> 00:47:52,462
Let them wait, man.
It ain't like we gonna be all day.

756
00:47:56,475 --> 00:47:58,466
All right.

757
00:48:00,445 --> 00:48:03,346
No, ma'am, it says right here--
His Honor had the Bureau of Solid Waste

758
00:48:03,382 --> 00:48:05,043
conduct a clean sweep
along Tivoly.

759
00:48:05,083 --> 00:48:07,278
But it took six months
before they showed up.

760
00:48:07,319 --> 00:48:09,310
Well yeah, okay,
but nobody's perfect.

761
00:48:09,354 --> 00:48:11,914
But hey, listen. I wouldn't be
sitting here if I didn't believe

762
00:48:11,957 --> 00:48:14,755
Clarence Royce wasn't truly committed
to this city and its people.

763
00:48:14,793 --> 00:48:16,556
What about the crime
in our neighborhood?

764
00:48:16,595 --> 00:48:18,222
I admit that's another
good point.

765
00:48:18,263 --> 00:48:21,858
But, lady,
between you and me, I can tell

766
00:48:21,900 --> 00:48:24,767
from your voice you're black and
you can tell from my voice I'm white.

767
00:48:24,803 --> 00:48:26,771
So I gotta ask you,

768
00:48:26,805 --> 00:48:29,501
when do you think the last time
a white man voted for a black man

769
00:48:29,541 --> 00:48:31,532
when there was another
white man in the race?

770
00:48:31,576 --> 00:48:33,476
I don't know, but you must
really believe in him.

771
00:48:33,512 --> 00:48:36,948
Well, ain't that what I been saying?
He's just the best candidate.

772
00:48:36,982 --> 00:48:39,610
- So you'll go with my man?
- I'll think about it.

773
00:48:39,651 --> 00:48:41,585
All right, that's great.
Thank you for your time.

774
00:48:41,620 --> 00:48:43,850
- Goodbye.
- All right.

775
00:48:53,665 --> 00:48:56,532
- I have a hall pass.
- Yeah, good for you.

776
00:49:39,611 --> 00:49:42,739
- Mine's down.
- Attaboy.

777
00:49:44,583 --> 00:49:48,576
You need bodies, Lester?
Here you go.

778
00:49:50,789 --> 00:49:55,192
We got a warrant and a teletype
for my boy Lex.

779
00:49:55,227 --> 00:49:58,560
So dead or alive, he's on file.

780
00:49:58,597 --> 00:50:00,656
And beyond that,
it's time for you to shine

781
00:50:00,699 --> 00:50:02,929
that mighty intellect of yours

782
00:50:02,968 --> 00:50:04,492
on some real murders, hmm?

783
00:50:04,536 --> 00:50:07,437
Give up the hypotheticals
and shit.

784
00:50:07,472 --> 00:50:09,872
Yeah, I suppose.

785
00:50:11,810 --> 00:50:14,040
This is my issue-- crime,

786
00:50:14,079 --> 00:50:16,172
and I understand completely
what you're saying.

787
00:50:16,214 --> 00:50:19,081
And if you give me the opportunity,
I will be able to do something to--

788
00:50:19,117 --> 00:50:21,881
to help you out and, you know,
other people in this neighborhood.

789
00:50:25,457 --> 00:50:28,551
Mr. Ricks,
thank you for your time

790
00:50:28,593 --> 00:50:30,185
- and for your attention.
- No problem.

791
00:50:30,228 --> 00:50:32,696
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

792
00:50:32,731 --> 00:50:35,825
Pretty brazen, shaking hands
with the enemy in broad daylight.

793
00:50:35,867 --> 00:50:39,894
- Werner's Deli this isn't.
- Definitely not.

794
00:50:39,938 --> 00:50:42,463
Though here you are, Councilman,
leaving no door unopened.

795
00:50:42,507 --> 00:50:44,338
Shoe leather--
our secret weapon.

796
00:50:44,376 --> 00:50:46,742
You surprised me.
You've made this a horse race.

797
00:50:46,778 --> 00:50:50,339
So uh, what makes me think you didn't
just happen by and find us here?

798
00:50:53,251 --> 00:50:55,446
Watkins is breaking
with the mayor.

799
00:50:55,487 --> 00:50:57,785
How do you know?

800
00:50:57,822 --> 00:51:01,758
I know. I've carried the mayor's water
because I had to, Councilman.

801
00:51:01,793 --> 00:51:04,261
I'd love to see some new blood
in this city.

802
00:51:04,296 --> 00:51:06,696
And I'd love the chance
to do the right thing

803
00:51:06,731 --> 00:51:09,063
for this police department
for a change.

804
00:51:28,186 --> 00:51:30,177
Wait until he turns
the corner.

805
00:51:33,258 --> 00:51:35,692
District office for Watkins--

806
00:51:35,727 --> 00:51:37,354
Gilmore Street.

807
00:51:37,395 --> 00:51:39,363
And fuck
them red lights, man.

808
00:51:45,670 --> 00:51:49,834
Not a place you expect
to find any gangsters--

809
00:51:49,874 --> 00:51:53,173
police, for that matter.

810
00:51:53,211 --> 00:51:57,113
- Heard you knew something I didn't.
- Told you before--

811
00:51:57,148 --> 00:51:59,912
I make it my business
to keep an ear to the ground.

812
00:51:59,951 --> 00:52:02,112
I make it my business
to do business.

813
00:52:02,153 --> 00:52:04,485
We doing business,
or are we just talking?

814
00:52:04,522 --> 00:52:06,183
And if it's talk,
I'ma walk.

815
00:52:06,224 --> 00:52:08,624
I heard the people pulling
security at the card game

816
00:52:08,660 --> 00:52:11,151
weren't too keen
on their wages.

817
00:52:11,196 --> 00:52:13,164
I figured it was
only a matter of time

818
00:52:13,198 --> 00:52:16,065
before they found a way
to get their due compensation.

819
00:52:16,101 --> 00:52:18,001
And you didn't think
to tell me?

820
00:52:18,036 --> 00:52:20,834
A man learns best
when he get burned.

821
00:52:20,872 --> 00:52:24,035
How do I know you ain't
making this shit up?

822
00:52:24,075 --> 00:52:27,135
You don't.
Things happen on the street.

823
00:52:27,178 --> 00:52:30,045
Proof is hard to come by.

824
00:52:33,418 --> 00:52:36,182
Go ahead, open it.

825
00:52:40,792 --> 00:52:42,191
Off the street,

826
00:52:42,227 --> 00:52:43,956
there's all kind of proof.

827
00:52:43,995 --> 00:52:47,021
They planning on executing
those Friday--

828
00:52:47,065 --> 00:52:49,033
time it with the election,
I guess,

829
00:52:49,067 --> 00:52:51,934
show they doing their job,
cleaning up the city,

830
00:52:51,970 --> 00:52:54,131
taking down a kingpin.

831
00:52:54,172 --> 00:52:56,606
- How did you come by this?
- Told you before--

832
00:52:56,641 --> 00:52:58,939
I keep my ear
to the ground.

833
00:52:58,977 --> 00:53:01,445
- What are you gonna do with it?
- Maybe nothing.

834
00:53:01,479 --> 00:53:04,277
Charlie's not part
of the co-op.

835
00:53:05,950 --> 00:53:07,884
Or maybe
I tip him for a fee.

836
00:53:07,919 --> 00:53:11,821
What do you think a man
with a whole lot of money

837
00:53:11,856 --> 00:53:15,155
would pay
for his freedom?

838
00:53:16,227 --> 00:53:19,287
You know, lately

839
00:53:19,330 --> 00:53:22,026
I come to find out someone trying
to take pictures of me.

840
00:53:22,067 --> 00:53:23,898
Pictures?

841
00:53:23,935 --> 00:53:25,698
Video.

842
00:53:25,737 --> 00:53:29,366
You heard anything about me
through your travels?

843
00:53:29,407 --> 00:53:31,534
Had no incentive to listen.

844
00:53:34,612 --> 00:53:36,477
You do now.

845
00:53:51,596 --> 00:53:53,461
It's one thing
to sit out the primary.

846
00:53:53,498 --> 00:53:55,227
It's another

847
00:53:55,266 --> 00:53:57,496
for me to turn
on Clarence Royce.

848
00:53:57,535 --> 00:54:00,129
- Granted.
- And if I did jump,

849
00:54:00,171 --> 00:54:02,935
why not land
behind Tony Gray?

850
00:54:02,974 --> 00:54:05,238
At least he's from
my side of the tracks.

851
00:54:05,276 --> 00:54:08,439
Tony can't win. I can.

852
00:54:10,081 --> 00:54:11,708
Look, the truth is,

853
00:54:11,750 --> 00:54:14,810
whatever I can do for you,
the mayor can match or double.

854
00:54:14,853 --> 00:54:17,083
I have a pretty good
grass-roots organization,

855
00:54:17,122 --> 00:54:19,113
but nothing even close
to his kind of money.

856
00:54:19,157 --> 00:54:21,717
Now, I'll ticket up
with anyone you want me to.

857
00:54:21,760 --> 00:54:25,025
I know you want Daniels in the 11th
and Stokes in the 10th.

858
00:54:25,063 --> 00:54:27,759
I'll keep away from any tickets
you think I might harm.

859
00:54:27,799 --> 00:54:30,962
I know I'm not everyone's idea
of a bargain on your side of town.

860
00:54:31,002 --> 00:54:33,300
- Hmm.
- But right now,

861
00:54:33,338 --> 00:54:35,329
a week from the primary,

862
00:54:35,373 --> 00:54:38,968
the fact is,
Royce and I both need you.

863
00:54:39,010 --> 00:54:43,310
After the election, the equation changes
for him but not for me.

864
00:54:43,348 --> 00:54:46,374
I'm a white mayor
in a majority-black city,

865
00:54:46,417 --> 00:54:48,385
and if I'm gonna
do anything--

866
00:54:48,419 --> 00:54:50,944
and, Delegate, I am so serious
about fixing this city--

867
00:54:50,989 --> 00:54:52,980
I'm gonna have to govern
by consensus.

868
00:54:53,024 --> 00:54:55,822
And if you support me, you will have
a voice within my administration

869
00:54:55,860 --> 00:54:58,420
simply because
I'm gonna need it.

870
00:55:00,965 --> 00:55:03,934
Last poll that
Clarence showed me,

871
00:55:03,968 --> 00:55:05,629
he was up
by seven points.

872
00:55:06,938 --> 00:55:10,101
Bullshit.
I'm within four.

873
00:55:15,313 --> 00:55:18,714
- You won't be needing that.
- I know.

874
00:55:20,718 --> 00:55:23,448
- Here?
- Yeah, here.

875
00:56:00,558 --> 00:56:02,890
Dag.

876
00:56:02,927 --> 00:56:04,895
Yo, turn it off-- the bulb
might have got too hot.

877
00:56:04,929 --> 00:56:06,590
Or the battery's dying.

878
00:56:07,732 --> 00:56:09,723
We should go back.

879
00:56:13,938 --> 00:56:17,465
- Yo, man, it stinks, man.
- Ain't like it was.

880
00:56:31,856 --> 00:56:33,221
See he ain't move.

881
00:56:36,961 --> 00:56:39,327
Yeah.

882
00:56:39,364 --> 00:56:41,764
Blood still stuck to his hair.

883
00:56:41,799 --> 00:56:46,293
- He dead?
- He dead.

884
00:56:46,337 --> 00:56:48,532
Lex too?

885
00:56:48,573 --> 00:56:52,270
He dead. They all is.
Feel better?

886
00:56:53,745 --> 00:56:55,975
Donut wrong, yo.

887
00:56:56,014 --> 00:56:57,777
Ain't no special dead.

888
00:56:59,951 --> 00:57:03,352
There's just dead.

9999
00:00:0,500 --> 00:00:2,00
